the smart, laconic Ed Ruscha retrospective at the Hirshhorn, you
may want to check out a few local art paths less traveled. By
Holland Cotter.
</P>
<P>
   NY-PHOTOGRAPHY (New York) _ If you want to know how far afield a
serious photographer will go in this city, you can get some idea at
the Museum of the City of New York, where ``New York Now 2000:
Contemporary Work in Photography'' offers 130 photographs of New
York City and New Yorkers. By Vicki Goldberg.
