<P>
   &UR; PUTIN'S SEA OF TROUBLES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PUTIN'S-WATERLOO-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The loss of 118 sailors on Russia's nuclear submarine, the Kursk
_ and the bungling that followed _ have dented President Vladimir
Putin's reputation for controlled efficiency and may yet make
Russians rethink the sort of government they deserve. After giving
the impression that he had a tightening grip on Russian affairs,
Putin and his administration seemed to be flailing about
hopelessly. &QL;
</P>
