the typical Internet user was a heterosexual white male younger
than 40. Although this characterization was mostly true, the Web is
now becoming a thriving marketplace for a wider range of people.
Asian-Americans, Hispanics, African-Americans, gay men and lesbians
and people with disabilities are double-clicking in greater
numbers. By David Kirby.
