<P>
   RELIGION-MUSIC _ At a time when the hymn book, choir and organ
are becoming endangered species in many churches in favor of the
ubiquitous praise band and modern worship choruses flashed on a big
screen, the contemporary Christian group 4 Him has released a
collection of traditional songs called ``Hymns: A Place of
Worship''. If any group could pull off giving the pop treatment to
such songs as It Is Well, Savior Like a Shepherd and Great Is Thy
Faithfulness, it would be 4 Him. (DAYTON DAILY NEWS). 20. WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITNESS _ Absence can be a better witness to God than
in-your-face-evangelism. But it tends to be Jews who use absence to
proclaim their faith. Most Christians don't bother. Many Jewish
merchants at trade shows leave their stalls barren on the Sabbath.
They sacrifice a day's sales to be obedient to the law of their
God. (Gushee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
