Machiavellian manipulation didn't help their image or cause either.
Can a corporate trainer's Survivor-scheming ways really work in the
real world? Is Mach-The-Knife really the corporate trainer of the
future? No way, says one local corporate training guru. ``Companies
want you to figure out how to make the organization work better.
Because that's what's going to pay off in the bottom line. You
wouldn't want an organization where there's one survivor and
everybody else has left.'' (Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
15.
