<P>
   WITNESS _ Absence can be a better witness to God than
in-your-face-evangelism. But it tends to be Jews who use absence to
proclaim their faith. Most Christians don't bother. Many Jewish
merchants at trade shows leave their stalls barren on the Sabbath.
They sacrifice a day's sales to be obedient to the law of their
God. (Gushee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
