u l BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT &LR;      08-25 0444
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
 ATTN: Style and Leisure Editors:  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service plans the following articles
from the Style section for use Sunday, Aug. 27, and thereafter.
</P>
<P>
   LOBBY-AROMATHERAPY (New York) _ What does the lobby of your
building smell like? Disinfectant? Wet dog? If you're one of the
purchasers of multimillion-dollar apartments in the Loft SoHo
building opening here in the fall, expect ylang-ylang and rose oil.
The idea was subtly to affect the mood of Lenny Kravitz and the
other extremely well-heeled residents, who will soon be closing on
apartments where aromatherapy hits them when they walk through the
door. The scents will change with the time of day and the season.
By Jennifer Steinhauer.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   JOURNALISM-CHIC (Undated) _ Is the Fifth Estate experiencing a
rehabilitation? NBC has a new fall series called ``Deadline,''
about a dapper columnist who solves crimes in his spare time.
Cameron Crowe, in his movie ``Almost Famous,'' opening Sept. 15,
recounts his days as a 15-year-old Rolling Stone writer during an
era when rock journalists could still pretend to be almost as cool
as their subjects. And in the pipeline, there's ``Serendipity,''
which began filming in New York last week, and may be the first
movie in which the dramatis personae include an obituary writer for
The New York Times. Not since Hoffman and Redford played a
better-looking Woodward and Bernstein has the profession been made
to look so cool. By Rick Marin.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   GAP-NEWLOOK (Undated) _ Filtering into Gap stores since
mid-July, when the chain sold off the last of its summer cargo
shorts, are lace-bordered tank tops, filmy skirts and leathers in
hothouse hues of carmine, pink and mauve. Clearly these
trend-driven looks were intended by the retailer to shake up
shoppers lulled into a torpor by last year's surfeit of khakis,
cargo pants and polo shirts. By Ruth La Ferla.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   NITEOUT-JOAN-JETT (New York) _ Nite out with Joan Jett, the
goddess of tight-leathered '80s rock, and a New York Liberty
fanatic. By Douglas Century.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Many a gardener grows coral bells, but
only a few do for the sake of their flowers. Not that coral bells
don't have lovely flowers. They do. They send up spikes covered
with small bell-shaped blossoms in colors from pure white to
purple-scarlet. The flowers, bobbing atop stems so slender they are
almost invisible, look as if they are floating above the plant, not
tethered to it at all. What's more, coral bells have an
extraordinarily long season of bloom for perennials. By Cass
Peterson.
</P>
