<P>
   GREIG-FILES _ Microscopes and telescopes. Bifocals and
binoculars. Sunglasses and magnifying glasses. Opera glasses and
lorgnettes. Humans will do anything to improve eyesight. Why?
Vision is a major player in the sensory game. This edition of the
Greig Files is the third installment in a series on the senses. So
grab those drugstore reading glasses and settle in. You are about
to find out why seeing is believing. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ ATLANTA _ Today we'll discuss rockers for a
baby crib, which aren't a big problem, and working with oak, which
can be a very big problem. Doug Williams wrote to say that ``We
have an antique baby crib from which the rockers were removed
before it came to us. ``I wish to build rockers for it. ``What are
your thoughts on the correct size and `rocking capability' for
these rockers?'' Williams went on to provide the dimensions of the
cradle and speculate on federal rules governing crib rockers.
Rockers on cribs, and rocking chairs for that matter, are really a
matter of aesthetics rather than any kind of mathematical formula.
(Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
