overcharging the suspects in the Worcester warehouse fire case? An
analysis. By Joanna Weiss. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FED-GREESNSPAN (Undated) _ Judging by the Fed's decision against
raising interest rates and comments about rising worker
productivity, Alan Greenspan may be a New Economy convert.
Expecting worker productivity to increase for some time to come in
the United States as technology investments continue, the Fed
chairman suggested the expansion will keep rolling along. By
Kimberly Blanton. 700 words. &QC;
</P>
<P>
   RAYTHEON-UNION (Undated) _ Large blue-collar union at Raytheon
Co. in Massachusetts could strike this weekend over pay and
job-security issues. The union has been riven by internal
squabbling and faces a federal lawsuit. By Ross Kerber. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECOMMERCE (Tokyo) _ Slow to embrace e-commerce and online
shopping, Japan is finally embarking on its own Internet
revolution. But it is doing so in a very Japanese way: at the
convenience store. By Sharon Moshavi. 1150 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) _ Patriots coach Bill Belichick
says he is concerned about the ``overall depth'' of the team. He's
faced with younger players on the end of the roster at virtually
every position. By Nick Cafardo. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-TRAVERS (Saratoga, N.Y.) _ This has been such a tumultous
season for the 3-year-olds, that the morning line favorite in the
