<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   VAUGHAN-REMEMBERED _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Austin remembers the day
Stevie Ray Vaughan died on its 10th anniversary. For many, the
moment they found out about the helicopter crash is unforgettable,
a la the JFK shooting. So are the candle-light vigil held that
night in Zilker and the Antone's blues jams over the next five
nights. However, it wasn't, as some have said, ``The day the music
died in Austin.'' In fact, the music thrived, as the upsurge of
Stevie's profile posthumously has also raised the profile for the
live music capital. We'll talk to local music figures, including
his ex-bandmates, about that day and how it still affects us today.
(Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
