   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet Travel page for the
current week. This layout is will be available Thursday by 2
p.m.)COXNET TRAVEL 0826: UNDERGROUND PARIS -- Think of Paris
landmarks, and monuments that stretch skyward come to mind: the
delicate Eiffel Tower, the gargoyle-bedecked Notre Dame and the
white domes of Sacre Couer. There is another Paris, too _ one
that's hidden beneath the boulevards, one that creeps adjacent to
the Seine. To experience it, you must descend. Down into the dark
and, later, back up to the City of Light. The Paris Metro, the
catacombs, the sewers . . . these are perhaps the most famous
sights of Underground Paris. (Sturrock, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 5-column color photo of the
entrance to the sewers and a 2-column color photo from inside the
sewers.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: IF YOU GO BOX -- A list of smart things to do when
visiting the sewers.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TRAVEL BRIEFS -- The opening of the American Discovery
Trail, the United States' first coast-to-coast, nonmotorized trail,
will be celebrated Sept. 2 in San Francisco, at Crissy Field in the
Presidio. Others. (N.Y. Times News Service)
</P>
<P>
   END COXNET PAGE
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-FITCAMP _ WAYNE COUNTY, Tenn. _ The hills are alive with
the sound of groaning. Yet no matter how much we wail, grunt and
pant, the rolling countryside around the Tennessee Fitness Spa
remains serene. It is another hot, still morning in a week of such
mornings, which means we're on another March of Pain.
</P>
<P>
   Teases to inside sidebars on spa suggestions from Spa Finders
and Conde Nast readers' spa favorites. Also teases ahead to
Tuesday's Healthy Living centerpiece on how people struggle to
maintain good fitness and diet habits after visiting a
spa.(Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
