<P>
   JOURNALISM-CHIC (Undated) _ Is the Fifth Estate experiencing a
rehabilitation? NBC has a new fall series called ``Deadline,''
about a dapper columnist who solves crimes in his spare time.
Cameron Crowe, in his movie ``Almost Famous,'' opening Sept. 15,
recounts his days as a 15-year-old Rolling Stone writer during an
era when rock journalists could still pretend to be almost as cool
as their subjects. And in the pipeline, there's ``Serendipity,''
which began filming in New York last week, and may be the first
movie in which the dramatis personae include an obituary writer for
The New York Times. Not since Hoffman and Redford played a
better-looking Woodward and Bernstein has the profession been made
to look so cool. By Rick Marin.
