mid-July, when the chain sold off the last of its summer cargo
shorts, are lace-bordered tank tops, filmy skirts and leathers in
hothouse hues of carmine, pink and mauve. Clearly these
trend-driven looks were intended by the retailer to shake up
shoppers lulled into a torpor by last year's surfeit of khakis,
cargo pants and polo shirts. By Ruth La Ferla.
