returned to the stock, which had been halted after a fake press
release disseminated a litany of false, negative news. The stock
early in the day sunk to $40. BY ARTHUR LOUIS. (running in main
news). &QL; 
 &QL; 
SURFING: As a growing generation of surfers struggles to juggle the
demands of career and family while trying to find time to indulge
in their passion for wave riding, Bay Area startups are keeping
them connected online to the surfing world while helping them
manage their time by forecasting when and where the waves will be
best. BY GREG AMBROSE. &QL; 
 &QL; 
